var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Article","page":"API","text":"Article\n\nBibTeX type for journal articles.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Article"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.BibEntry","page":"API","text":"BibEntry{T <: BibType}\n\nThis object represents a BibTeX entry.  It is a wrapper around pybtex's pybtex.database.Entry object, connecting it with its corresponding key.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.BibEntry"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.BibLibrary","page":"API","text":"BibLibrary\n\nThis provides a simple interface to read and manipulate BibTeX databases. Note that this is a full wrapper around the pybtex.database.BibliographyData class.  The underlying entries are stored as they are in the Python library.  The API provides helper functions to access common fields and properties, but the full entry objects are available for more advanced use cases.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.BibLibrary"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.BibType","page":"API","text":"This module provides the types used in the BibLibrary module. These are the general BibTeX types useful for dispatching entries on them.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.BibType"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Book","page":"API","text":"Book\n\nBibTeX type for whole books.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Book"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Booklet","page":"API","text":"Booklet\n\nBibTeX type for small printed works without a publisher.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Booklet"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Conference","page":"API","text":"Conference\n\nBibTeX type for conference-related publications.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Conference"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.InBook","page":"API","text":"InBook\n\nBibTeX type for a part of a book (e.g. chapter).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.InBook"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.InCollection","page":"API","text":"InCollection\n\nBibTeX type for a chapter or section in a collection.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.InCollection"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.InProceedings","page":"API","text":"InProceedings\n\nBibTeX type for an article in conference proceedings.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.InProceedings"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Manual","page":"API","text":"Manual\n\nBibTeX type for technical manuals.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Manual"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.MasterThesis","page":"API","text":"MasterThesis\n\nBibTeX type for a master's thesis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.MasterThesis"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Misc","page":"API","text":"Misc\n\nBibTeX catch-all type for miscellaneous entries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Misc"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.PersonName","page":"API","text":"PersonName\n\nStruct to represent a person's name with first, middle, last names and an optional suffix.\n\nFields\n\nfirstName::String : person's first name\nmiddleName::String : person's middle name(s)\nlastName::String : person's last name\nsuffix::String : optional suffix (e.g. \"Jr.\", \"III\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.PersonName"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.PhDThesis","page":"API","text":"PhDThesis\n\nBibTeX type for a doctoral dissertation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.PhDThesis"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Proceedings","page":"API","text":"Proceedings\n\nBibTeX type for conference proceedings volumes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Proceedings"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.TechReport","page":"API","text":"TechReport\n\nBibTeX type for technical reports.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.TechReport"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Thesis","page":"API","text":"Thesis\n\nGeneral BibTeX thesis type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Thesis"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Pybtex.Unpublished","page":"API","text":"Unpublished\n\nBibTeX type for unpublished works.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.Unpublished"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.eltype-Union{Tuple{Type{BibEntry{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API","text":"Base.eltype(::Type{BibEntry{T}}) -> T\n\nThis function returns the type of the BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.eltype"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.getindex-Tuple{BibLibrary, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"Base.getindex(db::BibLibrary, key::AbstractString) -> Any\n\nReturn the stored entry for a given key.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary : the library to query\nkey::AbstractString : bibtex key for the entry\n\nOutput\n\nthe stored entry (often a Python Entry or the wrapper expected by the API)\n\nExample\n\nentry = library[\"smith2020\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.getindex"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.getproperty-Tuple{BibLibrary, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"Base.getproperty(bib::BibLibrary, v::Symbol) -> Any\n\nProvide property access helpers for BibLibrary.\n\nInput\n\nbib::BibLibrary\nv::Symbol : property name; use :entries to access the underlying entries mapping\n\nOutput\n\nreturns bib.db.entries if v == :entries, otherwise falls back to getfield\n\nExample\n\nbib.entries  # access underlying storage\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.getproperty"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.haskey-Tuple{BibLibrary, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"haskeys(db::BibLibrary, keys::Vector{String}) -> Vector{Bool}\n\nCheck whether the given key exists in the library.\n\nFunction\n\nBase.haskey(db::BibLibrary, key::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\nkey::AbstractString\n\nOutput\n\nBool : true if present\n\nExample\n\nhaskey(library, \"smith2020\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.haskey"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.insert!-Tuple{BibLibrary, BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"insert!(db::BibLibrary, entry::BibEntry) -> Nothing\n\nInsert (or replace) a BibEntry into the library using its key.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\nentry::BibEntry : a BibEntry wrapper object (the whole entry is stored)\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : operation mutates db\n\nNotes\n\nThis implementation stores the whole BibEntry object under entry.key.\n\nExample\n\ninsert!(library, my_entry)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.insert!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.iterate-Tuple{BibLibrary}","page":"API","text":"Base.iterate(db::BibLibrary; state = 1) -> Union{Tuple{Any, Int}, Nothing}\n\nIterator for BibLibrary which yields stored entries.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\noptional state::Int for iterator position\n\nOutput\n\n(entry, next_state) or nothing when iteration finishes\n\nExample\n\nfor e in library\n\tprintln(e)\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.iterate"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.keys-Tuple{BibLibrary}","page":"API","text":"Base.keys(db::BibLibrary) -> Vector{String}\n\nReturn all keys present in the BibLibrary as a vector of String.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\n\nOutput\n\nVector{String} : list of bibkeys\n\nExample\n\ncollect(keys(library))\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.keys"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.length-Tuple{BibLibrary}","page":"API","text":"Base.length(db::BibLibrary) -> Int64\n\nReturn the number of entries in the database.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary : a BibLibrary instance\n\nOutput\n\nInt : number of entries stored\n\nExample\n\nlength(library)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.length"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.pop!-Tuple{BibLibrary, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"Base.pop!(db::BibLibrary, key::AbstractString) -> Any\n\nRemove and return the entry associated with key.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\nkey::AbstractString : key to remove\n\nOutput\n\nthe removed entry (or throws if not present)\n\nExample\n\nremoved = pop!(library, \"smith2020\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.pop!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.show-Tuple{IO, BibEntry{Pybtex.Article}}","page":"API","text":"Base.show(io::IO, entry::BibEntry{Article}) -> Nothing\n\nPretty-print a BibEntry{Article} to an IO stream.\n\nInput\n\nio::IO : output stream\nentry::BibEntry{Article} : article entry wrapper\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : prints formatted article metadata to io\n\nExample\n\nshow(stdout, article_entry)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.show-Tuple{IO, BibEntry{Pybtex.Book}}","page":"API","text":"Base.show(io::IO, entry::BibEntry{Book}) -> Nothing\n\nPretty-print a BibEntry{Book} to an IO stream.\n\nInput\n\nio::IO : output stream\nentry::BibEntry{Book} : book entry wrapper\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : prints formatted book metadata to io\n\nExample\n\nshow(stdout, book_entry)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.show-Tuple{IO, BibLibrary}","page":"API","text":"Base.show(io::IO, bib::BibLibrary) -> Nothing\n\nPretty-print a BibLibrary to an IO stream.\n\nInput\n\nio::IO : output stream (e.g. stdout)\nbib::BibLibrary : library to describe\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : prints a short summary to io\n\nExample\n\nshow(stdout, library)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.show-Tuple{IO, Pybtex.PersonName}","page":"API","text":"Base.show(io::IO, person::PersonName) -> Nothing\n\nFormat and print a PersonName to an IO stream.\n\nInput\n\nio::IO : output stream\nperson::PersonName : person structure with firstName, middleName, lastName, and optional suffix\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : prints the formatted name to io\n\nExample\n\nshow(stdout, author)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.show-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{IO, BibEntry{T}}} where T<:Pybtex.BibType","page":"API","text":"Base.show(io::IO, entry::BibEntry{T}) where {T<:BibType} -> Nothing\n\nPretty-print a generic BibEntry{T} to an IO stream.\n\nInput\n\nio::IO : output stream\nentry::BibEntry{T} : generic bib entry (type-specific fields will be shown when available)\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : prints formatted metadata to io\n\nExample\n\nshow(stdout, some_entry)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.show"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.values-Tuple{BibLibrary}","page":"API","text":"values(db::BibLibrary) -> Vector{Any}\n\nReturn a vector with all stored entries in the library.\n\nInput\n\ndb::BibLibrary\n\nOutput\n\nVector{Any} : list of stored entries\n\nExample\n\nvals = collect(values(library))\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.values"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.bibEntryToDict-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"bibEntryToDict(entry::BibEntry) -> OrderedDict{String, Any}\n\nThis function converts a BibTeX entry to an OrderedDict. The dictionary has the keys: key, type, and fields.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.bibEntryToDict"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getAbstract-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getAbstract(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the abstract of the publication, if available.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getAbstract"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getAdsUrl-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getAdsUrl(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the ADS URL of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getAdsUrl"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getAllFields-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getAllFields(entry::BibEntry) -> Vector{String}\n\nThis function returns all fields of a BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getAllFields"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getArxiv-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getArxiv(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nGet arXiv number, assuming it is in the eprint field.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getArxiv"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getAuthors-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getAuthors(entry::BibEntry) -> Vector{PersonName}\n\nThis function returns the authors of a BibTeX entry. The authors are returned as a vector of PersonName objects. If the authors field is not present, but editors are found, the editors are returned instead.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getAuthors"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getBibtex-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getBibtex(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the BibTeX representation of the entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getBibtex"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getBookTitle-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"This function returns the book title of a BibTeX entry, if available. This is common for conference proceedings.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getBookTitle"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getDoi-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getDOI(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the DOI of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getDoi"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getEId-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getEId(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the electronic identifier of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getEId"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getEdition-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getEdition(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the edition of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getEdition"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getEditors-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getEditors(entry::BibEntry) -> Vector{PersonName}\n\nThis function returns the editors of a BibTeX entry. The editors are returned as a vector of PersonName objects.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getEditors"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getEntry-Tuple{BibLibrary, Any}","page":"API","text":"getEntry(bib::BibLibrary, key::AbstractString) -> BibEntry\n\nReturn a BibEntry wrapper for the stored entry with key.\n\nInput\n\nbib::BibLibrary\nkey::AbstractString\n\nOutput\n\nBibEntry{T} where T corresponds to the BibTeX type\n\nExample\n\nentry = getEntry(library, \"smith2020\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getEntry"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getFileName-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getFileName(entry::BibEntry; libraryFolder::AbstractString = \"\") -> String or Vector{String}\n\nThis function returns the file name(s) of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getFileName"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getIsbn-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getIsbn(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the ISBN of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getIsbn"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getJournal-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getJournal(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the journal where the publication was published.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getJournal"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getKeywords-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getKeywords(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the keywords of the publication, if available.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getKeywords"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getLocation-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getLocation(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the location of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getLocation"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getNumber-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getNumber(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the number of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getNumber"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getPages-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getPages(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the pages of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getPages"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getPublisher-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getPublisher(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the publisher of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getPublisher"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getSchool-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getSchool(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the school of the publication, if available. This is common for theses.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getSchool"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getTitle-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getTitle(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the title of a BibTeX entry, if available.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getTitle"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getType-Union{Tuple{BibEntry{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API","text":"getType(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the type of a BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getType"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getTypeName-Tuple{Type{Pybtex.Article}}","page":"API","text":"getTypeName(::Type{T}) where {T<:BibType} -> String\n\nReturns the name of the type of the entry as a string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getTypeName"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getUrl-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getUrl(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the URL of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getUrl"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getVolume-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getVolume(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the volume of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getVolume"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.getYear-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"getYear(entry::BibEntry) -> String\n\nThis function returns the year of the publication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.getYear"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.hasField-Tuple{BibEntry, String}","page":"API","text":"hasField(entry::BibEntry, field::String) -> Bool\n\nThis function checks if a field is present in a BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.hasField"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.journalAbbreviationFromTag-Tuple{String}","page":"API","text":"journalAbbreviationFromTag(tag::String) -> String\n\nReturns the journal abbreviation from the tag. For example, the tag \"apj\" returns \"Astrophys. J.\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.journalAbbreviationFromTag"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.journalFullNameFromTag-Tuple{String}","page":"API","text":"journalFullNameFromTag(tag::String) -> String\n\nReturns the journal full name from the tag. For example, the tag \"apj\" returns \"Astrophysical Journal\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.journalFullNameFromTag"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.journalTagFromFullName-Tuple{String}","page":"API","text":"journalTagFromFullName(fullName::String) -> String\n\nReturns the journal tag from the full name. For example, the full name \"Astrophysical Journal\" returns \"apj\". This is essentially an inversion of journalFullNameFromTag.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.journalTagFromFullName"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.numberOfAuthors-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"numberOfAuthors(entry::BibEntry) -> Int64\n\nThis function returns the number of authors of a BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.numberOfAuthors"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.numberOfEditors-Tuple{BibEntry}","page":"API","text":"numberOfEditors(entry::BibEntry) -> Int64\n\nThis function returns the number of editors of a BibTeX entry.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.numberOfEditors"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.pybtexToPersonName-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"pybtexToPersonName(author) -> PersonName\n\nConverts a Pybtex person object to a PersonName object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.pybtexToPersonName"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.readBibtexDataBase-Tuple{String}","page":"API","text":"readBibtexDataBase(filename::String) -> BibLibrary\n\nRead a BibTeX file and return a BibLibrary.\n\nInput\n\nfilename::String : path to a .bib file\n\nOutput\n\nBibLibrary : parsed database\n\nExample\n\nlibrary = readBibtexDataBase(\"examples/sample.bib\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.readBibtexDataBase"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.removeCurlyBracesLimiters-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"removeCurlyBracesLimiters(s::AbstractString) -> String\n\nThis function fixes the strings from the bibtex file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.removeCurlyBracesLimiters"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.stringPy2Jl-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"This unexported function converts a python string to a julia string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.stringPy2Jl"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Pybtex.writeBibtexDataBase-Tuple{BibLibrary, String}","page":"API","text":"writeBibtexDataBase(bib::BibLibrary, filename::String) -> Nothing\n\nWrite a BibLibrary to a BibTeX file.\n\nInput\n\nbib::BibLibrary : library to write\nfilename::String : output path\n\nOutput\n\nNothing : writes file to disk\n\nNotes\n\nPerforms a post-processing replacement pass to clean common LaTeX sequences.\n\nExample\n\nwriteBibtexDataBase(library, \"clean.bib\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Pybtex.writeBibtexDataBase"},{"category":"section","location":"#Pybtex.jl-Documentation","page":"Home","text":"This library wraps the pybtex Python API so that Julia code can read, query, and rewrite BibTeX files without leaving the Julia REPL.","title":"Pybtex.jl Documentation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"Activate the project or add the package:\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(; path = \".\")  # when developing locally\nInstall the Python dependency:\npython -m pip install pybtex\nInstantiate the Julia environment:\njulia --project=. -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate()'","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Usage-overview","page":"Home","text":"Use readBibtexDataBase(\"path/to/file.bib\") to load a .bib file into a BibLibrary.\nFetch entries with getEntry(library, \"key\") and inspect fields with utilities such as getTitle, getJournal, getDOI, getFileName, getAllFields, and getBibTeX.\nWhen a field is missing, the helpers return an empty string instead of throwing (except getBookTitle, which currently assumes the booktitle field exists).\nPrint entries or libraries directly; the custom Base.show implementations format the most common fields nicely.","title":"Usage overview"},{"category":"section","location":"#Key-APIs","page":"Home","text":"Function Description\nreadBibtexDataBase(path) Load a BibTeX file into a BibLibrary.\nwriteBibtexDataBase(library, path) Serialize the library back to BibTeX while cleaning up LaTeX escapes.\ngetEntry(library, key) Wrap a single entry as a BibEntry typed by its BibTeX type.\ngetTitle, getJournal, getYear, getDOI Field helpers that clean braces and \\ escape sequences.\ngetAuthors, getEditors Return vectors of PersonName records derived from pybtex persons.\ngetFileName(entry; libraryFolder=\"\") Normalize BibTeX file entries into Julia paths.\ngetBibTeX(entry) Re-export the entry back to its BibTeX string.\ngetAllFields(entry) List all defined fields for an entry.","title":"Key APIs"},{"category":"section","location":"#Examples-and-sample-data","page":"Home","text":"See examples/examples.jl for a quick demonstration of how the library is used.\nThe accompanying sample database (examples/sample.bib) exercises the major entry helpers.","title":"Examples and sample data"},{"category":"section","location":"#Testing","page":"Home","text":"Run the bundled tests with:\njulia --project=. -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); Pkg.test()'\nThe tests live under test/runtests.jl and require the pybtex Python package in the active Python environment.","title":"Testing"},{"category":"section","location":"#Continuous-integration","page":"Home","text":"GitHub Actions run the same test command inside .github/workflows/ci.yml on every push and pull request.\nThe workflow also installs pybtex via pip, so the Julia job has the required Python dependency.","title":"Continuous integration"}]
}
